"title": "6755: union with Christ, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6755: union with christ, nature of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The nature of the union of Jesus Christ with believers is explained using a number of central images. The NT stresses the reality, closeness and considerable benefits of this union.</p>\n<h2>A covenantal relationship</h2>\n<h3>OT background</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5-Isa54:8\">ISA 54:5–54:8</a></strong> <em>The marriage covenant is used to illustrate the intimacy of the relationship between God and his people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:14\">JER 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:7\">HOS 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:16\">HOS 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>In the NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31-Eph5:32\">EPH 5:31–5:32</a></strong></p>\n<h2>A relationship deepened through the incarnation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:7–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14-Heb2:18\">HEB 2:14–2:18</a></p>\n<h2>A relationship personally entered through faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:11\">JHN 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:38\">JHN 7:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:31\">ACT 16:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:22\">ROM 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1\">ROM 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:9-Rom10:10\">ROM 10:9–10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:17\">2CO 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:16\">GAL 2:16</a></p>\n<h2>A relationship enriched through the sacraments</h2>\n<h3>Baptism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:3-Rom6:5\">ROM 6:3–6:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:27\">GAL 3:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:8\">ROM 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11-Col2:12\">COL 2:11–2:12</a></p>\n<h3>The Lord's Supper</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:26–26:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:22–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:17-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:17–22:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:16\">1CO 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:29\">1CO 11:23–11:29</a></p>\n<h2>A relationship that affects every aspect of life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:17\">1CO 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:1-John15:8\">JHN 15:1–15:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:20-John17:26\">JHN 17:20–17:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9-Rom8:11\">ROM 8:9–8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:19–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></p>\n<h2>It is a mysterious relationship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:27\">COL 1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:32\">EPH 5:32</a></p>",
